^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Okay, lets first discuss why I did not bid 1N instead of 3C. It was close, and I would not quarrel with 1N. Being short in the majors and with 5 clubs, I felt 3C was better. 80% of the time when pard opens 1C they have at least  a 4 card suit. So, 80% of the time we have a 9+ card fit and 3C is more preemptive, and makes it harder for the opponents to find their major. In this case, I preempted partner, but that is not usually the case, and she was able to bid 3N anyway. |
PG| ***** 94 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Next to discuss is the opening lead. In general, I find 4th best works out the best against NT, unless the suit was bid by the opponents. With Lisa's hand, I would have lead a low heart. She should not lead a club, as that is our suit. It is almost never right to lead the opponents suit. Had Lisa led a heart, 3N is a bit harder, as they take 2H 1C and 1D at least. And they might get a second spade. So, I do recommend 4th best from longest and strongest in NT|
